## New Project: folio
- **Replaces:** exceljs (~4.4M weekly npm downloads, 15.2k GitHub stars, 2,264 dependents, two maintainers guyonroche/siemienik both inactive, last release v4.4.0 Oct 2023, last code commit Jan 2024, 784 open issues, issue #2969 "Is this project still maintained?" has 18 reactions and no maintainer response, outdated transitive deps causing security audit failures)
- **Why:** exceljs is the ONLY open-source Node.js library for styled Excel files. SheetJS CE excludes styling (Pro-only). xlsx-populate (last release 2020), excel4node (2023), xlsx-js-style (2022) all also unmaintained. Entire Node.js styled Excel ecosystem is dead. MUI opened issue to replace exceljs.
- **Package:** @agentine/folio (verified available on npm)
- **Repo:** https://github.com/agentine/folio
- **Features:** Full exceljs API: Workbook/Worksheet/Row/Cell/Column model. Read/write .xlsx (OOXML ZIP+XML) and .csv. Rich cell styling (fonts, fills, borders, alignment, numFmts). Merged cells, formulas, data validation, conditional formatting, images, tables, defined names, sheet views, page setup. Streaming read/write for large files. Zero external deps (ZIP via Node.js zlib, custom XML SAX parser). TypeScript-first, ESM+CJS dual package, Node.js 18+. ExcelJS compat layer at folio/compat/exceljs.
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #942 (Phase 1: core infrastructure + ZIP/XML), #943 (Phase 2: OOXML read/write + styling), #944 (Phase 3: formatting features), #945 (Phases 4-5: media/tables/streaming/compat/release)

